Petros to Invest $950 Million in Oil Industry, O Globo Says

-- B y   P e t e r   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-06-09T13:18:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/petros-to-invest-950-million-in-oil-industry-o-globo-says.html
Fundacao Petrobras de Seguridade
Social,  Brazil ’s second-biggest pension fund, plans to make
equity investments worth 1.5 billion reais ($950 million) in
Brazil’s oil and gas industry, Petros President Luis Carlos Afonso told  O Globo  in an interview.  Petros is also interested in investing in shipyards, ports
and airports, the Rio de Janeiro-newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Millard in Rio de Janeiro at 
